</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236B6877AFFDCFF54F60E3201FAE0" blockId="14.[151,1437,1143,1386]" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D35877AFFDCFED3F60E3169FB18" authority="Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[272,639,1144,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Montina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B939EAA4877AFFDCFED3F60E3279FB1B" box="[272,367,1144,1169]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">Montina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B47877AFFDCFEB7F60E3169FB18" author="Amyot, C. J. B. &amp; Serville, J. G. A." box="[372,639,1144,1170]" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" refId="ref8380" refString="Amyot, C. J. B. &amp; Serville, J. G. A. (1843) Histoire naturelle des insects: Hemipteres. Librairie Encyclopedique de Roret. Fain et Thunot, Paris, 681 pp." type="book" year="1843">Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
currently includes ten species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B47877AFFDCFC19F60E3788FB18" author="Maldonado C." box="[986,1182,1144,1170]" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" refId="ref9399" refString="Maldonado C., J. (1990) Systematic catalogue of the Reduviidae of the World, Caribbean Journal of Science. Special publication No. 1. University of Puerto Rico, Mayaguez, 694 pp." type="book" year="1990">Maldonado 1990</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B47877AFFDCFB73F601363AFB18" author="Stal, C." box="[1200,1324,1143,1170]" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" pagination="66 - 128" refId="ref9724" refString="Stal, C. (1872) Enumeratio Reduviinorum Americae. In: Enumeratio Hemipterorum. Kongliga Svenska VetenskapsAkademiens Handlingar, 10, 66 - 128." type="journal article" year="1872">Stål (1872)</bibRefCitation>
separated 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D35877AFFDCFF54F6EA32ADFB3C" authority="Stal, 1859" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1859" box="[151,443,1179,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Montina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="B939EAA4877AFFDCFF54F6EA3252FB3C" box="[151,324,1180,1206]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">Montina lobata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B47877AFFDCFE89F6ED32ADFB3C" author="Stal, C." box="[330,443,1179,1206]" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" pagination="175 - 204" refId="ref9700" refString="Stal, C. (1859) Till kannedomen om Reduvini. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 16, 175 - 204." type="journal article" year="1859">Stål, 1859</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D35877AFFDCFE33F6EA30A2FB3C" authority="(Lepeletier &amp; Serville, 1825)" authorityName="Lepeletier &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1825" baseAuthorityName="Lepeletier &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1825" box="[496,948,1179,1206]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Montina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinuosa">
<emphasis id="B939EAA4877AFFDCFE33F6EA317DFB3F" box="[496,619,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">M. sinuosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B47877AFFDCFDBBF6EA30BAFB3C" author="Lepeletier, A. L. M. &amp; Serville, J. G. A." box="[632,940,1179,1206]" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" pagination="1 - 832" refId="ref9312" refString="Lepeletier, A. L. M. &amp; Serville, J. G. A. (1825) Histoire naturelle. Entomologie. In: Olivier, G. A., Encyclopedie Methodique. Vol. 10. Agasse, Paris, pp. 1 - 832." type="book chapter" year="1825">Lepeletier &amp; Serville, 1825</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D35877AFFDCFB6FF6EA361DFB3F" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1196,1291,1180,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Montina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B939EAA4877AFFDCFB6FF6EA361DFB3F" box="[1196,1291,1180,1205]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">Montina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the connexival margins from third to fifth (actually, segments IV–VI) abdominal segments which are distinctly enlarged as rounded lobes (
<figureCitation id="13762A33877AFFDCFEA7F69232A3FB74" box="[356,437,1251,1278]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–37" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1949,1974]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,184,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,170,1938]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 32–37. Figs. 32–33. Montina lobata, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm, 32, female, 33, male. Figs. 34–35. Montina sinuosa, female, 34, dorsal view, scale bar 5.0 mm, 35, abdomen, lateral view, scale bar 2.0 mm. Figs. 36–37. Zelus lewisi, female, dorsal view, 36, scale bar 5.0 mm, 37, head and thorax, scale bar 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3239893/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) (versus with at most prominent posterolateral corners in the other species of the genus). In relation to 
<collectingCountry id="F35A7626877AFFDCFEF0F77E3284FAA8" box="[307,402,1288,1314]" name="Ecuador" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, besides some records of unidentified species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D35877AFFDCFC03F77E3709FAAB" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[960,1055,1288,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Montina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B939EAA4877AFFDCFC03F77E3709FAAB" box="[960,1055,1288,1313]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">Montina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the only species recorded at this country was 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D35877AFFDCFEE5F75A3056FACC" authority="(Stal, 1866) (Froeschner 1981)" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1866" baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[294,832,1323,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Reduviidae" genus="Montina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fumosa">
<emphasis id="B939EAA4877AFFDCFEE5F75A32CBFACC" box="[294,477,1324,1350]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">Montina fumosa</emphasis>
(Stål, 1866) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDC4B47877AFFDCFDB5F75A3021FACC" author="Froeschner, R. C." box="[630,823,1324,1350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="516" pagination="1 - 147" refId="ref8729" refString="Froeschner, R. C. (1981) Heteroptera or true bugs of Ecuador: a partial catalog. Smithsonian contributions to Zoology, 322, 1 - 147." type="journal article" year="1981">Froeschner 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the two species cited here are new records to 
<collectingCountry id="F35A7626877AFFDCFF77F7263202FAE0" box="[180,276,1360,1386]" name="Ecuador" pageId="14" pageNumber="516">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
